initial_story:
The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.

The World Championship of Dance is kicking off in Tokyo, Japan, and this year's excitement is unmatched. Check out the schedule for live matches and rehearsal footage.

The United States is debuting a powerhouse tap dance team, Storm and Co., who will wow audiences with their intricate routine, Time is Ticking.

Ahead of the competition, we caught up with team captain Olivia Winters to talk nerves, training, and their game-changing choreography. How do they plan to keep up the energy with no breaks?

Catch all the action live on PBS and Stream now app on Saturday, June 1st!

The international culinary showdown, Taste Quest, is heating up in Mumbai, India! This year's event promises unparalleled flavors and cooking techniques. Get the schedule for live broadcasts and kitchen cam highlights.

Germany is set to unleash their secret spice masterminds, Schenke and Sons, who will tantalize taste buds with their innovative curry recipe, Flaming Blaze.

Ahead of the cook-off, we interviewed Chef Julian Weber to discuss stress, seasoning, and his daring culinary approach. What unexpected ingredients have they added to this year's winning dish?

The highly anticipated Global Fork Fest is serving up a storm in Tokyo, Japan! As culinary giants gather, get ready to salivate over the delectable fusion of east meets west.
